channel.title: Space to Ground Video Podcasts
channel.description: A short weekly wrap-up of the latest news and science from the International Space Station.
channel.itunes:subtitle: Weekly Update From the International Space Station
channel.itunes:keywords: NASA, International Space Station, Astronauts, space station, Soyuz
channel.itunes:author: National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA)

item.title: Space to Ground: Round Three: 12/6/2019
item.description: There is never a dull moment onboard the orbiting laboratory. There were three spacewalks to fix a cosmic particle detector and now two space cargo ships are on their way to the station.

item.title: Space to Ground: Keeping it Cool: 11/29/2019
item.description: The Expedition 61 crew enjoyed a Thanksgiving feast ahead of another spacewalk set for this Monday. A European experiment also tests controlling a rover on Earth from the station.

item.title: Space to Ground: History Made: 10/18/2019
item.description: Throughout spaceflight history, 14 women have completed spacewalks. On October 18, Jessica Meir brought that number up to 15 when she floated outside the airlock alongside 4-time spacewalker Christina Koch for the first all-female extravehicular activity.

item.title: Space to Ground: History's Greatest Adventure: 07/19/2019
item.description: 50 years ago flight controllers managed history's greatest adventure. Astronauts Christina Koch and Nick Hague reflected on the historic moon landing ahead of the arrival of a new crew Saturday.

item.title: Space to Ground: Farm-to-Table: 07/12/2019
item.description: Astronauts have been growing fresh produce on station. This week some of that food will return to Earth for analysis. The crew also performed an experiment to investigate time perception in space.

item.title: Space to Ground: On the Bubble: 07/05/2019
item.description: The crew explored radiation exposure in space ahead of the 4th of July holiday. The astronauts also sent down an Independence Day message as the station nears 20 years of continuous human presence.

item.title: Space to Ground: Back on Terra Firma: 06/28/2019
item.description: Three residents of the space station safely returned to planet Earth, but not before another station crewmember sequenced DNA to explore how damaged DNA repairs itself in space.

item.title: Space to Ground: Tending the Hive: 06/21/2019
item.description: Astrobee, a free-flying robot, took its first spin around the station. The crew also released four small cube satellites from different countries into low earth orbit.

item.title: Space to Ground: Open for Business: 06/14/2019
item.description: NASA opens the station for commercial business as the crew worked on the BioNutrients experiment to provide astronauts with necessary vitamins on future long duration missions

item.title: Space to Ground: Release the Dragon: 06/07/2019
item.description: Two cargo spacecraft departed from the space station this week. Also, the crew installed an experiment to continue studying plant growth in space for future long duration missions.

item.title: Space to Ground: Saluting an Icon: 05/31/2019
item.description: Two cosmonauts wished the world's first spacewalker a Happy Birthday during their own spacewalk this week. The rest of the crew is loading the SpaceX Dragon cargo craft with science for return to Earth on Monday.

item.title: Space to Ground: The ABCs of DNA: 5/24/19
item.description: NASA astronaut Nick Hague is exploring how space radiation damages DNA and how the cell repair mechanism works in microgravity.

item.title: Space to Ground: Watching the Earth Breathe: 05/17/2019
item.description: A new science experiment will allow scientists to monitor carbon dioxide emission hotspots from space. Also the kidney cells experiment will examine how microgravity affects the health of the kidney.

item.title: Space to Ground: Reservations for Seven: 05/10/2019
item.description: The SpaceX Dragon became the sixth spaceship at the station Monday delivering about 5,500 pounds of supplies. Also, researchers are exploring microalgae as a dietary boost for future astronauts going to the moon by 2024.

item.title: Space to Ground: The Droids You're Looking For: 05/03/2019
item.description: With the station back to full power, SpaceX is ready to launch their 17th resupply mission. Astrobee, a new free-flying robot will assist the crew with chores on board station.

item.title: Space to Ground: Extreme Exposure: 04/26/2019
item.description: Since the arrival of the U.S. Cygnus space freighter the crew has been unloading the new cargo, including a new air scrubber system, and new materials to be tested in the harsh environment of space.

item.title: Space to Ground: Marathon Mission: 04/19/2019
item.description: The U.S. Cygnus space freighter delivered new science today that will challenge future scientists. Also, Christina Koch's will stay in space until February 2020 and new astronauts Jessica Meir and Drew Morgan are now due to launch to the station.

item.title: Space to Ground: Extended Duration: 04/12/2019
item.description: Two astronauts completed the third spacewalk of the year. The first crewed Boeing flight has been extended to a full-duration expedition. Also, results from the One-Year Mission Twins Study are in!

item.title: Space to Ground: Express Delivery: 04/05/2019
item.description: A Russian cargo ship brought food, fuel and supplies to station this week. Meanwhile, two astronauts get ready to complete the last of three spacewalks to upgrade the batteries on station.

item.title: Space to Ground: Power Walking: 03/29/2019
item.description: This week two astronauts conducted the second in a series of three spacewalks to upgrade the space station's power storage capacity. Also, did you know there have been over 2500 experiments on the Space Station?

item.title: Space to Ground: Stepping Out: 03/22/2019
item.description: Two spacewalkers are working outside today to upgrade the space station's power storage capacity.

item.title: Space to Ground: Fire in the Sky: 03/15/2019
item.description: Three new crew members arrived at the station after six hours in the Soyuz spacecraft, bringing the crew complement back to six.

item.title: Space to Ground: A New Era: 03/08/2019
item.description: This week the crew welcomed the SpaceX Crew Dragon to the station, after completing it's five day mission Dragon undocked and returned to Earth.

item.title: Space to Ground: An American Dawn: 03/01/2019
item.description: This week astronauts onboard the station have been preparing for a special visitor.

item.title: Space to Ground: Personal Space: 02/22/2019
item.description: Astronauts are preparing an experiment that will test the ability to store fuel for long duration missions. The crew also conducted leak checks to ensure their space suits are in proper working condition.

item.title: Space to Ground: Femtosatellites: 02/08/2019
item.description: A U.S. cargo craft departed the station today. Now it will deploy CubeSats before reentering Earth's atmopshere. Next, NASA is preparing for commercial crew missions.

item.title: Space to Ground: Packing and Prepping: 02/01/2019
item.description: A U.S. spaceship is being packed with trash before it leaves the station next week and students are teaming up with the crew for a high-flying robotics competition.

item.title: Space to Ground: A Second Chance
item.description: Nick Hague will launch again with Alexey Ovchinin, this time taking NASA astronaut Christina Koch with them. Back in space, two cosmonauts went for a spacewalk to inspect a Soyuz crew ship before it returns to Earth.

item.title: Space to Ground: Four Orbits Later: 12/7/2018
item.description: A new crew reached the station Monday faster than a flight from New York to London! The SpaceX Dragon resupply ship launched this week too carrying over a ton of science experiments.

item.title: Space to Ground: Constructive Ideas: 11/30/2018
item.description: Watching cement dry in space? It could impact the construction of future lunar or Martian habitats. Plus a new crew and cargo are due at the station next week.

item.title: Space to Ground: The Beginning of Tomorrow: 11/23/2018
item.description: The International Space Station celebrated 20 years in space and the crew feasted for Thanksgiving after a pair of space deliveries this week. #SpaceToGround

item.title: Space to Ground: Honoring a Legend: 11/16/2018
item.description: Two space deliveries, one in honor of a legendary U.S. astronaut, are launching to the space station this weekend carrying supplies and goodies for the crew just in time for the holidays. #SpaceToGround

item.title: Space to Ground: Surviving the Plunge: 11/09/2018
item.description: The crew said farewell to a Japanese spaceship this week. The resupply ship will send protein crystal samples back to Earth before it burns up over the Pacific Ocean Saturday.

item.title: Space to Ground: Getting a Grip: 11/04/2018
item.description: Astronauts are teaching scientists how they grip and manipulate objects in space to help engineers design inteligent controls and interfaces aboard spacecraft. NASA also delivered the first 8K video of the crew working in space this week. ​

item.title: Space to Ground: Neutron Dance: 10/26/2018
item.description: The Expedition 57 Commander got fired up for science this week working on gear that studies flames and gases. Outside the station, a device is making the study of pulsars NICER.

item.title: Space to Ground: A Successful Failure: 10/19/2018
item.description: Two crew members are safe following an aborted ascent to space last week. Meanwhile, science continues on the station as NASA astronauts get familiar with SpaceX hardware and facilities.

item.title: Space to Ground: Kounotori 7: 09/28/2018
item.description: A Japanese supply ship, loaded with new science and supplies, was captured at the station on Thursday. The crew will soon unpack the new Life Sciences Glovebox that will help us better protect space explorers on long voyages.

item.title: Space to Ground: Long Distance Call: 09/21/2018
item.description: Ivanka Trump visited Johnson Space Center with NASA Administrator Jim Bridenstine and talked to the Expedition 56 crew. The astronauts also checked U.S. spacesuits ahead of upcoming spacewalks.

item.title: Space To Ground: Above the Storm: 09/14/2018
item.description: A Japanese cargo craft is set to lift off today to the station after a typhoon caused delays. The Expedition 56 crew also shared spectacular imagery Hurricane Florence.

item.title: Space to Ground: Batteries Included : 09/07/2018
item.description: The Expedition 56 crew is getting ready for the arrival of a Japanese cargo craft next week and a pair of spacewalks soon afterward. A space fan also wants to know if astronauts play sports in space.

item.title: Space to Ground: Potential Game Changer: 08/31/2018
item.description: The BEST experiment is studying how life adapts in space and has the potential to be a game changer. Meanwhile, pressure is holding steady on the station after the crew patched up a small hole on a Soyuz spaceship.

item.title: Space to Ground: ICARUS Ascending: 08/17/2018
item.description: Two spacewalkers installed an animal tracker outside the station this week. A study inside the station is observing how liquids behave in the open cabin of the orbital lab.

item.title: Space to Ground: A Star to Steer By: 08/10/2018
item.description: Astronauts on the space station are testing an device that guided sailors for centuries and sharing space science lessons plans with teachers on Earth.

item.title: Space to Ground: From American Soil: 08/03/2018
item.description: NASA assigned nine astronauts to the first flights of the Boeing and SpaceX commercial crew vehicles. Dragon also departed the space station with over 3,800 pounds of cargo for return to Earth.

item.title: Space to Ground: Locally Grown: 07/27/2018
item.description: The Expedition 56 crew aboard the space station harvested plants and explored microbes this week to help astronauts in space and humans on Earth.

item.title: Space to Ground: Concrete Science: 07/20/2018
item.description: The Cygnus space freighter took out more than 6,600 pounds of trash this week and the crew studied the microstructure of cement possibly Earth and space habitats.

item.title: Space to Ground: Same Day Delivery: 07/13/2018
item.description: From cancer treatment research in space to a fast-track cargo shipment, the space station was a hot-bed of activity this week.

item.title: Space to Ground: Meet CIMON: 07/06/2018
item.description: The station crew has a new AI-based assistant called CIMON delivered on Dragon this week. CIMON is a test case possibly offering space-based solutions to astronauts on future long-term missions.

item.title: Space to Ground: Rocket's Red Glare: 06/29/2018
item.description: Dragon lit up the sky when it blasted off on a three-day journey to the station. A new experiment it is delivering will help us undertand how plants respond to water and stress as astronauts learn how to grow food in space.

item.title: Space to Ground: Clearing the Cosmos: 06/22/2018
item.description: Junk is a growing problem in space and a new satellite is exploring ways to clean it up. Also, a pollution and fire safety study has been reignited on the space station after some soot cleaning.

item.title: Space to Ground: Enhancing the View: 06/15/2018
item.description: Drew Feustel moved into third place for all-time spent spacewalking. He and Ricky Arnold installed high definition cameras to provide views of the SpaceX Dragon Crew and Boeing Starliner spacecraft.

item.title: Space to Ground: Launches and Landings: 06/08/2018
item.description: One crew returns to Earth, another crew launches to space while two astronauts get ready for a spacewalk to outfit the space station in support of commercial crew spacecraft.

item.title: Space to Ground: Handoff: 06/01/2018
item.description: Expedition 55 comes to a close as Commander Anton Shkaplerov hands control of the station today to NASA astronaut Drew Feustel. Meanwhile, the crew is staying busy with new experiments delivered aboard Orbital ATK's Cygnus cargo craft.

item.title: Space to Ground: Cold Hard Science: 05/25/2018
item.description: ORBITAL ATK’S ANTARES LIFTED OFF ON MONDAY MORNING, ILLUMINATING THE VIRGINIA NIGHT SKY AND DELIVERING THE CYGNUS SPACECRAFT INTO ORBIT.

item.title: Space to Ground: Kilauea Volcano: 05/18/2018
item.description: The Expedition 55 crew wrapped up the fifth spacewalk of the year this week and photographed the Kilauea Volcano ash plume on Hawaii.

item.title: Space to Ground: Ready for a Walk: 05/11/2018
item.description: This week on #SpaceToGround, the crew worked on an experimental furnace that levitates, melts and solidifies materials while also preparing for the 210th spacewalk at the space station.

item.title: Space to Ground: Color of the Sun: 04/27/2018
item.description: The station crew welcomed the new Administrator of NASA and nourished small organisms living on the orbital lab for space research this week on #SpaceToGround.

item.title: Space to Ground: Operating an Outpost: 04/20/2018
item.description: NASA released a free e-book describing how flight directors operate the station and the astronauts studied unique molecules vital to the design of newer, more stable product mixtures. #SpaceToGround

item.title: Space to Ground: Genes in Space: 04/13/2018
item.description: This week on #SpaceToGround, the crew explored how living in space impacts the relationship between DNA alterations and a weakened immune system while materials outside the station are being exposed to microgravity to see how they stand up to the extreme thermal environment.

item.title: Space to Ground: A Learning Doubleheader: 04/06/2018
item.description: The SpaceX Dragon delivered almost 5,800 pounds of experiments and station gear and the crew also harvested and consumed some space-grown lettuce, this week on #SpaceToGround.

item.title: Space to Ground: Upgrading the Outpost: 03/30/2018
item.description: The Expedition 55 crew wraps up a spacewalk and turns its attention to next week's arrival of the SpaceX Dragon resupply ship on #SpaceToGround this week.

item.title: Space to Ground: Night Launch: 03/23/2018
item.description: On #SpaceToGround this week, three Expedition 55-56 crew members will arrive at the space station today two of whom will go on a spacewalk just six days later.

item.title: Space to Ground: Neuromapping: 03/16/2018
item.description: This week on #SpaceToGround, a busy week aboard the space station had the crew exploring how fluids behave in space and studying what happens to an astronaut's brain on a long-term mission.

item.title: Space to Ground: A Unique Experience: 03/09/2018
item.description: This week on #SpaceToGround, we're improving how we cultivate crops in space to feed crews on long-term missions. Also, Flight Engineer Scott Tingle talked about extreme astronaut training with students from the University of Massachusetts-Dartmouth.

item.title: Space to Ground: Home at Last: 03/02/2018
item.description: One crew is home safe, one crew is orbiting Earth and another crew is preparing for launch, this week on #SpaceToGround.

item.title: Space to Ground: Successful Spacewalk: 02/23/2018
item.description: After a short but successful spacewalk last week three Expedition 54 crew members now turn their attention to a return to Earth. #SpaceToGround

item.title: Space to Ground: Light Storm: 02/16/2018
item.description: A Russian resupply ship delivered more than three tons of cargo, two U.S. spacewalkers transferred a pair of older robotic hands and a NASA astronaut talked to Texas students this week on #SpaceToGround.

item.title: Space to Ground: Some Serious Science: 02/08/2018
item.description: The Expedition 54 crew studied gaseous flames and is learning how to grow edible crops on the space station this week. Also, Europe's lab module turned 10 this week!

item.title: Space to Ground: Prepping for a Spacewalk: 01/19/2018
item.description: SOME STATION SCIENCE HAS SUCCESSFULLY RETURNED TO EARTH, AND NOW CREWMEMBERS ARE GEARING UP FOR A PAIR OF SPACEWALKS FOCUSING ON THE ROBOTIC ARM.

item.title: Space to Ground: Down to Earth: 12/15/2017
item.description: Three Expedition 53 crew members have returned to Earth and the SpaceX​ Dragon cargo craft has blasted off for a Sunday rendezvous at the station. #SpaceToGround

item.title: Space to Ground: California Wildfires: 12/08/2017
item.description: Orbital ATK's Cygnus left the station this week packed with its heaviest load and the astronauts pictured the California wildfires burning 250 miles beneath them.

item.title: Space to Ground: Packing Up: 12/01/2017
item.description: The Orbital ATK​ Cygnus resupply ship is packed with over 5,500 pounds of trash and ready to leave Dec. 6 to burn up over the Pacific Ocean.

item.title: Space to Ground: The Big Meal: 11/23/2017
item.description: “MY PLANS FOR THANKSGIVING, INCLUDE JUST LIKE NORMAL, EATING LOTS OF FOOD AND TAKING A NAP. BUT SERIOUSLY, THE MOST IMPORTANT THING UP HERE IS THE COMRADERIE OF OUR CREWMATES. WE’RE GOING TO SHARE A MEAL TOGETHER FOR SURE.”

item.title: Space to Ground: Stuffed with Science: Nov. 17, 2017
item.description: CYGNUS LAUNCHED INTO ORBIT TO THE INTERNATIONAL SPACE STATION ON AN ANTARES ROCKET ON NOVEMBER 12th, CARRYING NEARLY 7,400 POUNDS OF CREW SUPPLIES, EQUIPMENT AND SCIENTIFIC RESEARCH TO SUPPORT EXPEDITION 53 AND 54 CREW MEMBERS.

item.title: Space to Ground: 200th Episode: 11/10/2017
item.description: IT’S BEEN A BLAST BRINGING YOU TO OUTER SPACE EACH WEEK FOR 200 EPISODES AND WE LOOK FORWARD TO DOING IT FOR A FEW HUNDRED MORE.

item.title: Space-to-Ground: One Orbit: 10/27/2017
item.description: This week on #SpaceToGround, astronauts and cosmonauts camped out for a full 90 minute orbit around the world. While the crew photographed the world from above, citizens of Earth took pictures of their daily lives from the ground. #1world1orbit

item.title: Space to Ground: Out the Door: 10/06/2017
item.description: One spacewalk down and two more to go this month. The crew is also growing a variety of fresh food for harvest in a few weeks. #SpaceToGround

item.title: Space to Ground: Triple Spacewalk: 09/29/2017
item.description: The Vice President called the Expedition 53 crew members this week as they prepared for three spacewalks taking place in October. #SpaceToGround

item.title: Space to Ground: Busy Crew: 09/22/2017
item.description: After releasing the SpaceX Dragon full of cargo for return to Earth, the crew now turns its attention to three upcoming spacewalks in October.

item.title: Space to Ground: Tracking a Monster: 9/8/2017
item.description: Three station crew members returned to Earth last week as Texas recovers from Hurricane Harvey. Another monstrous hurricane, Irma, was pictured from the space station.

item.title: Space to Ground: A Closer Look: 8/11/17
item.description: When there are 12 human eyes in space you need to check your vision. You also need supplies and Dragon is bringing them next week.

item.title: Space to Ground: A Stunning Launch: 8/4/2017
item.description: The station has new crew members and they are studying what space is doing to their bodies. You can also follow them on social media.

item.title: Space to Ground: A New Method: 07/27/2017
item.description: Mission Control will monitor a new crew launching Friday to the station. The crew on the station studied how liquids and gases mix in space.

item.title: Space to Ground: Summer Road Trip: 07/14/2017
item.description: The astronauts levitated cells with magnets this week and learned how to maximize their space exercise. In case you didn't know, the crew sets their clocks to Greenwich Mean Time.

item.title: Space to Ground: Celebrating Freedom: 07/07/2017
item.description: The crew sent home the SpaceX​ Dragon and celebrated Independence Day this week gazing at Earth's own spectacular light show.

item.title: Space to Ground: Solar Array Away!: 06/30/2017
item.description: The crew heads into the weekend having jettisoned a new type of solar array and researching how living in space may accelerate the aging process.

item.title: Space to Ground: Roll 'Em: 06/23/2017
item.description: LIKE BACK TO BACK VACATIONS OR A BIG SUMMERTIME MOVE, THE SPACE STATION CREW IS SPENDING THEIR DAYS UNPACKING AND RE-PACKING TOO.

item.title: Space to Ground: A NICER Look: 06/16/17
item.description: A Russian cargo ship docked to the station after a two-day trip. The station is also getting a NICER look at neutron stars.

item.title: Space to Ground: Cargo Inbound-Crew Outbound : 06/02/2017
item.description: The SpaceX​ Dragon launch was delayed to Saturday and two Expedition 51 crew members landed on Earth Friday after 196 days in space.

item.title: Space to Ground: Surprise Spacewalk!: 05/26/2017
item.description: Two astronauts went on a surprise spacewalk this week while another studied how a crew adapts to space using virtual reality.

item.title: Space to Ground: A Fleet of CUBESATS: 05/19/2017
item.description: A VERITABLE FLEET OF SMALL SATELLITES WERE SLINGSHOT INTO ORBIT FROM STATION THIS WEEK.

item.title: Space-to-Ground: A Short Time Ago: 05/05/2017
item.description: Astronauts spent the week learning how bones change in space and on Earth and studied how fuel behaves in spacecraft tanks.

item.title: Space to Ground: American Record-Holder: 4/28/17
item.description: PEGGY WHITSON IS NOW THE RECORD HOLDER FOR MOST TIME IN SPACE FOR AN AMERICAN.

item.title: Space to Ground: Bullseye: 04/14/17
item.description: THIS WEEK, HALF OF THE INTERNATIONAL SPACE STATION'S INHABITANTS DEPARTED THE ORBITING COMPLEX AND LANDED SAFELY IN KAZAHKSTAN.

item.title: Space to Ground: Prepare For Landing: 04/07/2017
item.description: A NASA astronaut and two Roscosmos cosmonauts are set end their mission in space on Monday after 173 days on orbit.

item.title: Space to Ground: Return of the Dragon: 03/24/2017
item.description: SPACEX'S DRAGON SPLASHED DOWN ON MARCH 19, MARKING THE END TO ITS TENTH RESUPPLY MISSION.

item.title: Space to Ground: At Home in Space : 03/10/2017
item.description: HE SAGE-III EXPERIMENT MEASURES THE EARTH’S SUNSCREEN, OR OZONE, WHICH IS IMPORTANT TO PROTECTING LIFE ON OUR PLANET.

item.title: Space-to-Ground: Science Time: 03/03/2017
item.description: A ton of science arrived at the station last week including a stem cells study to improve disease treatments on Earth. #SpaceToGround

item.title: Space to Ground: Special Delivery for the Station: 02/24/2017
item.description: Two spaceships from opposite sides of the world, a Dragon and a Progress, launched to the space station this week delivering science and supplies.

item.title: Space to Ground: Who Doesn't Enjoy a Good View of Planet Earth?: 02/10/2017
item.description: Japan could soon be providing striking high-def Earth views from the station. NASA Astronaut Peggy Whitson​ also celebrated her birthday in space this week!

item.title: Space to Ground: Science Touchdown: 2/3/2017
item.description: IT FELT LIKE A TWO MINUTE DRILL ON STATION THIS WEEK WITH THE SCIENCE COMING FAST AND FURIOUS.

item.title: Space to Ground: Satellites Away!: 01/20/2017
item.description: Six small satellites shot away from the station this week as the crew studied liquids to improve water and fuel systems in space.

item.title: Space to Ground: A Recharging Spacewalk!: 01/13/2017
item.description: A pair of astronauts and robotics controllers continued working this week to recharge the space station's power systems.

item.title: Space to Ground: A Powerful Spacewalk: 1/6/2017
item.description: Nothing like robots and spacewalks to get the New Year started.

item.title: Space to Ground: 2016: A Space Expedition: 12/22/2016
item.description: 2016 WAS PACKED WITH INCREDIBLE EVENTS ON THE STATION, SO LET’S COVER A FEW HIGHLIGHTS, STARTING WITH THE SCIENCE.

item.title: Space to Ground: Holiday Delivery: 12/15/2016
item.description: THE JAPANESE HTV-6 WAS GRAPPLED BY THE EXPEDITION 50 CREW THIS WEEK.

item.title: Space to Ground: Cargo on the Way! 12/09/2016
item.description: THE JAPANESE HTV-6 LIFTED OFF FROM THE TANEGASHIMA SPACE CENTER IN JAPAN ON FRIDAY MORNING.

item.title: Space to Ground: 70 Hours of Science: 12/01/2016
item.description: PRELIMINARY INFORMATION FROM ROSCOSMOS INDICATES THE PROGRESS 65 WAS LOST OVER AN UNPOPULATED AND MOUNTAINOUS AREA WITH MOST OF THE CRAFT BURNING UP IN THE ATMOSPHERE.

item.title: Space to Ground: Giving Thanks for a New Crew: 11/23/2016
item.description: SPACE STATION COMMANDER SHANE KIMBROUGH TOOK SOME TIME TO SHOW US WHAT THE CREW WILL BE EATING ON THE BIG DAY.

item.title: Space to Ground: That's No Moon: 11/17/2016
item.description: RISING SLOWLY BEHIND THE ROCKET CARRYING PEGGY WHITSON, OLEG NOVITSKIY AND THOMAS PESQUET TO SPACE, THE SUPERMOON MADE A DRAMATIC APPEARANCE AT THE BAIKONUR COSMODROME IN KAZAKHSTAN.

item.title: Space to Ground: Eyes on Earth: 11/10/2016
item.description: COMMANDER SHANE KIMBROUGH WORKED ACROSS SEVERAL DAYS REPLACING PARTS IN THE OXYGEN GENERATION SYSTEM,A KEY COMPONENT OF THE STATION’S LIFE SUPPORT.

item.title: Space to Ground: Picture Perfect Landing: 11/3/2016
item.description: Three explorers returned to Earth and the new station commander checked out U.S. spacesuits this week. Also, a space fan wants to know how astronauts measure the radiation they are exposed to.

item.title: Space-to-Ground: Three Up, Three Down: 10/27/2016
item.description: The International Space Station saw three new crew members arrive last Friday and will see another trio leave Saturday night. Also, the crew is growing red romaine lettuce again.

item.title: Space to Ground: Smoke and Fire: 10/20/2016
item.description: ORBITAL ATK KICKED THINGS OFF WITH THEIR TRIUMPHANT RETURN TO THE WALLOPS FLIGHT FACILITY.

item.title: Space to Ground: Astronaut Energy: 10/14/2016
item.description: It takes a lot of energy every day to be an astronaut: performing complex science experiments and maintenance tasks, working out two and a half hours all while on a packed timeline.

item.title: Space-to-Ground: A Churning Storm: 10/07/2016
item.description: The station trained its cameras on Hurricane Matthew this week while Orbital ATK​ scheduled its sixth Cygnus cargo mission to launch on Oct. 13.

item.title: Space to Ground: Knock Knock: 9/30/2016
item.description: KATE RUBINS GOT HANDS ON THIS WEEK WITH ONE OF THE STATION’S BIGGEST EXPLORATION TECHNOLOGY DEMOS.

item.title: Space to Ground: Launch Delay: 9/26/2016
item.description: The next crew to visit the space station is awaiting a new launch date while the astronauts in space are studying how liquids and solids interact potentially benefiting the pharmaceutical industry.

item.title: Space to Ground: Be Cool: 9/16/2016
item.description: SPACE TECH IS TAKING A PAGE FROM THE PLAYBOOK OF THE YEAR 200 B.C.

item.title: Space to Ground: Tracking the Tropics: 9/2/2016
item.description: TWO SPACEWALKS IN TWO WEEKS? CHECK.

item.title: Space to Ground: A Gateway for Future Spacecraft: 8/19/2016
item.description: Two astronauts wrapped up spacewalk this week to install a new adapter for future space vehicles to dock to on the outside of the International Space Station.

item.title: Space to Ground: Well Suited for a Spacewalk: 08/12/2016
item.description: JEFF WILLIAMS AND KATE RUBINS SPENT THE WEEK PREPARING FOR THEIR TRIP OUT INTO SPACE SCHEDULED FOR AUGUST 19. TO GET READY.

item.title: Space to Ground: Taking a Breather: 08/05/2016
item.description: This week the Expedition 48 crew explored how astronaut's breathe in space and are gearing up for a high school competition using self-contained, bowling ball-sized satellites called SPHERES.

item.title: Space to Ground: From the Heart: 7/29/2016
item.description: KATE RUBINS STARTED THE HEART CELLS EXPERIMENT THAT LOOKS AT WHAT HAPPENS TO THE HEART MUSCLES IN SPACE DURING LONG-DURATION MISSIONS.

item.title: Space to Ground: Double Down: 7/22/2016
item.description: TWO SPACECRAFT. THOUSANDS OF POUNDS OF CARGO. ONE BUSY CREW.

item.title: Space to Ground: New Crew, New Ride: 7/8/2016
item.description: Kate Rubins, Anatoly Ivanishin, and Takuya Onishi launched from Baikonur, Kazakhstan and are now on a 2-day trip to the station.

item.title: Space to Ground: 3D Printing in Zero G: 7/1/2016
item.description: It can be quite a hassle to ship tools to space, and could take months or even years of planning and execution. so, why not just make tools in orbit?

item.title: Space to Ground: Touchdown!: 6/24/2016
item.description: Expedition 47 crew members Tim Kopra, Tim Peake and Yuri Malenchenko landed safe and sound over the weekend completing 186 days in space.
